orted token usage for a typical document stays within configured per-call budget.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior requires real provider-reported usage, which depends on actual model/provider tokenization and live AI API response metadata; mocks can falsely pass (MOCK-HIDE yes, LLM-DEP default yes for real AI call path). Rejected Integration because stubbed usage numbers cannot validate real provider usage.","test_description":"Execute real classification calls for representative documents and assert provider-reported token usage metadata is <= configured budget; fail on any over-budget live report.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"On provider rate-limit signals, module waits and retries instead of surfacing immediate error.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is orchestration across retry policy, timing/backoff, and client call sequencing (module interaction). Real network is not required; in-process fake provider + fake clock can reproduce 429/Retry-After behavior (REAL-INFRA no). Rejected Agentic because correctness is retry control flow, not model decision quality.","test_description":"Wire classifier with retry middleware and fake clock; simulate provider rate-limit response then success; assert wait/backoff is applied and final result is returned without exposing intermediate rate-limit error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.17,"Integration":0.69,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
